  "prompt": "Why does Facebook give playstore update daily?",
  "response": "Facebook (Meta) doesn't actually update the app daily on the Google Play Store. Updates are typically released for various reasons, such as:\n\n1. Bug fixes and performance improvements\n2. Security patches\n3. New features or functionality\n4. Compatibility with latest Android versions\n5. User interface enhancements\n6. Addressing reported issues\n\nThe frequency of updates can vary depending on the development team's ongoing work and user feedback. While updates might seem frequent, they're not necessarily released every single day. If you're experiencing frequent update notifications, it could be due to:\n\n- Minor incremental updates\n- Background optimizations\n- A/B testing of new features\n- Continuous improvement of the app\n\nTo manage app updates, you can:\n- Set app updates to automatic\n- Choose to update only on Wi-Fi\n- Manually control when updates occur\n- Disable automatic updates\n\nIf updates are bothering you, you can adjust your Play Store settings or app update preferences.",
